title: Number of High Level Consumer Services, Tajikistan 2005
name: Number of High Level Consumer Services, Tajikistan 2005
description:
This is a shapefile of the number of high level consumer services by jamoat in Tajikistan from the United Nation's Jamoat Capacity Mapping Project of 2005. The data ranges from zero to five per jamoat and is assigned a numerical value 0-4. Data was uploaded as shp, dbf, and shx files. 
The Capacity Mapping Survey is a survey of local capacities including those of local Jamoat administrations,civil society and private sector. UNDP designed this survey with the participation of international community and local NGOs of Tajikistan dealing with local development.

The assessment of capacities allows development planners to understand professional skills capacity and assets, compare information from different Jamoats and identify trends that allow for better performance in designing a strategic development plan.

Although the focus of previous capacity mapping surveys has been on the areas covered by the Jamoat. The survey in 2006 focusing on local government capacities will include a survey of District government capacities as well.
